pageContext.claim: “I don't know who they are. I mean, I guess maybe I met them or maybe I took pictures with them, because I saw there was a picture of me with them and others. But I take pictures with a lot of people. I don't know them. I don't know who they are, Jeanine.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump suggested that his only interaction with two Florida business executives and associates of Trump attorney Rudolph W. Giuliani were posed meet-and-greet photographs. But The Washington Post reported they had a 90 minute dinner in April, 2018, with Trump at the Trump Washington hotel with a small group of donors. "One of the men, Lev Parnas, has described to associates that he and his business partner, Igor Fruman, told Trump at the dinner that they thought the U.S. ambassador to Ukraine was unfriendly to the president and his interests," the Post said. "According to Parnas, the president reacted strongly to the news: Trump immediately suggested that then-Ambassador Marie ­Yovanovitch, who had been in the Foreign Service for 32 years and served under Democratic and Republican presidents, should be fired, people familiar with his account said."
